messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 12/2/05 7:55:28 PM,
janddplus5@... writes:


-=-yes I am signed in but I think it is just not open
on the site
yet. I googled the info and that is what I came up
with. Something
about Jelly world opening in 2006.-=-


You have to type it in in the search box after you're
logged on. I just delete the end of the address and
put in jell...

and then my computer fills in the rest. But it's
jelly/jelly.phtml

Another ending to add to get free stuff (and I keep
forgetting about it, but someone posted it an
unschooling.info today) is /freebies

No phtml ending.

From whatever neopets page you're on, like
http://www.neopets.com/desert/sakhmet.phtml

Up in the box on your browser that shows what page
you're on, erase the end of it up to .com/
so it's

http://www.neopets.com/
then type at the end
freebies

http://www.neopets.com/freebies

and hit "go" or "enter" or "return" or whatever your
computer likes. <g>

That doesn't work over once a month, and maybe not
even that often (someone here probably knows).

Sandra
